name: market for waste polyethylene terephthalate, for recycling, unsorted | waste polyethylene terephthalate, for recycling, unsorted | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/16562/documentation

This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for  'waste polyethylene terephthalate, for recycling, unsorted', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.

Activity starts with the collection of unsorted waste PET for recycling.

This activity includes input of collection containers and transportation requirements to the sorting/recycling facility
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/381:Waste collection/3811:Collection of non-hazardous waste

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: Europe without Switzerland, US, CH.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Uncertainty estimation according to the pedigree matrix
